[[Image:54 Nancy bibliothèque municipale - vue générale.JPG|thumb|right|Public Library, Nancy, France, 2009]]
The '''Bibliothèque municipale de Nancy''' (est. 1750) is a [[public library]] in [[Nancy, France]]. It houses approximately 400,000 documents, books, maps, plans and prints. Polish king [[Stanisław Leszczyński]] began the collection in 1750.<ref>{{cite book |title=American Library Annual: 1914-1915 }}</ref> The library is located in a 1769 building of the historical University of Nancy. At 43, rue Stanislas, it is close to the [[Place Stanislas]] and the [[Gare de Nancy-Ville]].

