'''Game Software Rating Regulations''' ({{zh|c=遊戲軟體分級管理辦法|p=Yóuxì ruǎntǐ fēnjí guǎnlǐ bànfǎ}}), also translated as '''Game Software Rating Management Regulations''', is the [[video game content rating system]] used in [[Taiwan]], [[Hong Kong]] and [[Southeast Asia]]. The law was established on 6 July 2006 and amended 29 May 2012.<ref name=GSRR>{{cite web|title=Game Software Rating Management Regulations|url=http://www.gamerating.org.tw/gsgi_way.php|work=Taiwan Game Software Rating Information|publisher=Digital Game Rating Committee|accessdate=19 September 2013}}</ref>
== Ratings == The system uses five ratings:<ref name=GSRR></ref>
{| class="wikitable" |- !Abbreviation !Rating |- |[[File:GSRR R logo.svg|80px]] |限制級 (Restricted) (R) – Only persons of age 18 and above may use such software. |- |[[File:GSRR PG 15 logo.svg|80px]] |輔15級 (Parental Guidance 15) (PG 15) – Only persons of age 15 and above may use such software. |- |[[File:GSRR PG 12 logo.svg|80px]] |輔12級 (Parental Guidance 12) (PG 12) – Only persons of age 12 and above may use such software. |- |[[File:GSRR P logo.svg|80px]] |保護級 (Protected) (P) – Only persons of age 6 and above may use such software. |- |[[File:GSRR G logo.svg|80px]] |普遍級 (General Public) (G) – All ages may use such software. |- |}
