{{coord|43|44|37|N|7|25|54|E|display=title|region:MC_type:landmark}}
[[File:Monaco07.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Grimaldi Forum]]
The '''Grimaldi Forum''' in [[Monaco]] is a conference and congress centre located on the seafront of Monaco's eastern beach quartier, [[Larvotto]]. [[Les Ballets de Monte Carlo]] and the [[Monte-Carlo Philharmonic Orchestra]] regularly perform there. This is also the venue of the [[EVER Monaco]] exhibition held March annually.<ref>[http://conference.evermonaco.com/everconference_uk/venue.php EVER will take place in Monte-Carlo, Monaco]</ref>

During the renovation of [[Salle Garnier]] in the [[Opéra de Monte-Carlo]] in 2004–05, operas were presented at the [[Salle des Princes]] in the Grimaldi Forum.<ref>[http://www.opera.mc/ History of the Monte-Carlo Opera]</ref>

The Grimaldi Forum also hosts the draw for the group stage, last 32 (Europa League only), last 16, quarter finals, and semi-finals of the [[UEFA Champions League]], [[UEFA Europa League]], and the [[UEFA Best Player in Europe Award]].

