{{Infobox book| <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = I Can See the Sun | image = The sunny night russian edition.jpg | title_orig = მე ვხედავ მზეს | translator = | author = [[Nodar Dumbadze]] | cover_artist = | country = [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] | language = [[Georgian Language|Georgian]] | series = | genre = [[novel]] | publisher = | release_date = [[1962 in literature| 1962]] | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover|Hardback]]) | pages = 205 pages | isbn = }}
'''''I Can See the Sun''''' ({{lang-ka|მე ვხედავ მზეს}}) is a second novel written by [[Nodar Dumbadze]] in 1962. <ref>[https://www.livelib.ru/book/1000478030 Я вижу солнце — Нодар Думбадзе<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[https://www.amazon.co.uk/sun-story-Nodar-Vladimirovich-Dumbadze/dp/B0006D1TV0 I see the sun. A story: Amazon.co.uk: Nodar Vladimirovich Dumbadze, Fainna Glagoleva: Books<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> In 1965 Georgian director [[Lana Gogoberidze]] made a film with same name based on this novel.<ref>http://www.geocinema.ge/en/index.php?filmi=194</ref>
The story of novel set in the war years and it describes the difficult situation in the villages and the fear people felt for their loved ones who were fighting at the front. Sosoia is teenager who loves blind Khatia, which will be cured in the finale of the plot.
