{{Infobox tunnel | name = Koznitsa | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | line = [[Sofia]]–[[Karlovo]] | location = | coordinates = | os_grid_ref = | system = | start = | end = | stations = | startwork = | opened = {{start date|1951|06|06}} | owner = [[National Railway Infrastructure Company]] | construction = 1949–1951 | length = 5,808.5&nbsp;m | notrack = [[Single track (rail)|single track]] | gauge = {{RailGauge|sg}} ([[standard gauge]]) | el = 25&nbsp;kV | speed = | hielevation = 818&nbsp;m | lowelevation = 798&nbsp;m | height = | width = | grade =2.0‰ / 6.4‰ | map = {{Location map | Bulgaria |relief=1 |label = |position = |lat_deg = 42 |lat_min = 41 |lat_sec = 54 |lon_deg = 24 |lon_min = 22 |lon_sec = 55 |mark = Tunnel.png |width = 260}}}} '''Koznitsa''' is a railway tunnel under the [[Koznitsa (ridge)|Koznitsa ridge]] in the [[Balkan Mountains|Stara planina]] (Balkan Mountains), the longest tunnel in [[Bulgaria]]. The tunnel is located between the Bulgarian towns of [[Koprivshtitsa]] and [[Klisura (Bulgaria)|Klisura]] and is 5,808&nbsp;m long.<ref>{{cite book |title=Електрифицираните железници на България, т. 1 (1903-1995) |last1=Рулев |first1=Димитър |last2=Марков|first2=Минчо |location= София |year=2007 |pages=276 |language=Bulgarian}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title= Железопътната мрежа в България 1866-1975 |last=Деянов |first=Димитър |authorlink= |coauthors= |year=2005 |publisher=изд. "Булхаус" Стара Загора |location=София |isbn=954-9364-05-4 |pages=224 |url= |accessdate= |language=Bulgarian}}</ref> It is the seventh tunnel on the [[Sofia]]–[[Karlovo]] line, starting at the exit of Koprivshtitsa station and ending just before Stryama station. Along its entire length the tunnel is straight and at Koprivshtitsa the lights of the locomotive are visible a long distance into the tunnel. {{Citation needed|date=February 2007}}
