The '''N'Goussa district''' is an [[Algeria]]n administrative district in the [[Ouargla Province|Ouargla]] province. Its chief town is located on the eponymous commune of [[N'Goussa]].<ref name=":osm">{{Cite web|url=https://www.openstreetmap.org/relation/6822388|title=N'Goussa District|last=|first=|date=|website=OpenSteetMap|publisher=OpenSteetMap|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=12 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sirismm.si.edu/siris/coordinates.txt|title=coordinates.txt|last=|first=|date=|website=siris|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=12 May 2018}}</ref>
== Communes == The district is composed of only one commune: [[N'Goussa]].
