[[File:DvoracKraljaNikole.gif|thumb|300px|Nikšić Royal Palace]]

'''Nikšić Royal Palace''' is a (former) royal [[residence]] in [[Nikšić ]], [[Montenegro]]. The two-storied palace was built by king [[Nikola I Petrović-Njegoš]] in 1890. However, it was rarely used. Currently, it houses the Zavičajni Muzej (County Museum), documenting the historical development of the city.

