{{For|regional cable television company started by Jim Fitzgerald in 1964|Total TV, Inc.}} {{Infobox company | name = TotalTV | logo = TotalTV logo.svg | logo_size = | type = [[Subsidiary]] | foundation = 2006 | location = [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]] | area_served = [[Serbia]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Croatia]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]], [[Montenegro]], [[Slovenia]], [[Europe]] | subsid = | key_people = | parent = [[Serbia Broadband|SBB]] | industry = [[Mass media|Media]] | services = [[Broadcasting]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | num_employees = | homepage = [http://www.totaltv.tv www.totaltv.tv] | intl = }}
'''TotalTV''' is Serbian [[Direct To Home]] (DTH) platform, offering over 80 digital TV channels via satellite. Owner of platform is the largest Serbian cable operator [[Serbia Broadband|SBB]].
TotalTV is using the [[NDS Group]] [[VideoGuard]] system of scrambling. Platform is broadcast via [[Eutelsat]] 16A satellite (16.0E). In addition to [[Serbia]], TotalTV is also available in [[Slovenia]], [[Montenegro]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Croatia]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]] and Europe.
==TotalTV outside Serbia== Except for the originating country [[Serbia]], TotalTV is also available in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Montenegro]], [[Croatia]], [[Slovenia]] and [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]]. Every country has their own package of TV stations. [[File:Total TV.gif|right|thumb|100px|Old TotalTV logo.]]
It is technically and legally possible to use TotalTV in other countries as well, like [[Italy]], [[Germany]], [[Spain]], [[France]] etc. All of those countries have satellite signal coverage of the platform's [[satellite]].<ref>http://www.totaltv.tv/Total+TV/9/International.shtml</ref>
==Competition== The main DTH competitor of TotalTV in [[Serbia]] is the [[Digi TV]] platform from [[Romania]]. TotalTV claims they have 170.000 subscribers in Serbia, 59.000 in Montenegro and about 120.000 in Bosnia and Herzegovina, whereas DigiTV claims 100.000 subscribers in Serbia.
